Gains <@eb.key>Invisibility</> while in Reeds

A Sarkaz Caster captain responsible for protecting the Feranmut's skeleton, capable of hiding within turbulences in spacetime. When defeated within range of a Bloodcalling Altar, will return to the field when affected by the altar's Pulse Wave.
When blowing at full force, fires ranged attacks in all 4 directions, dealing <@eb.key>high Physical damage</> to allies hit. These attacks can be blocked by Realigned Flux
A colossus born of Mudrock's Arts and infused with ancient Sarkaz shamanistic Arts, it is an extension of its owner's will.
After a few attacks, the next attack deals splash damage in a cross; Attacks deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</> when <@eb.key>passionate variation</> is active
After a few attacks, the next attack hits an additional target; Attacks deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</> when <@eb.key>passionate variation</> is active
A mercenary specializing in anti-armor combat. After firing a single-use <@eb.key>super long-ranged grenade</>, charges at <@eb.key>high speed</>.

After a few attacks, the next attack restores a set amount of HP based on ATK; Instead restores the HP of this unit and all enemies in the surrounding 8 tiles when <@eb.key>passionate variation</> is active
ATK continuously increases when unblocked, resets on next attack; Attacks inflict a long <@eb.key>Stun</> to targets when <@eb.key>melancholic variation</> is active
Rolls in one direction after deployment, stunning enemies it hits for 1 second as well as clearing out any creep on the ground.
A Sea Terror that floats in the air and has sated its hunger. Its body contains a blazing-hot organ. Attacks inflict additional <@eb.key>Nervous Impairment</>.
After a few attacks, the next attack deals damage to all targets in range; <@eb.key>Attack range</> increases when <@eb.key>passionate variation</> is active
Attacks nearby <@eb.key>Throttle Valves</>; gains <@eb.key>Invisibility</> when on Blighted tiles
Takes up <@eb.key>4 Block</>; DEF and RES reduced when damage is taken; when destroyed, releases <@eb.key>'Traffic Officer'</> and self-destructs, dealing physical damage to nearby units
While in battle, reborn creations have <@eb.key>increased ATK</>, and their attacks will additionally deal <@eb.key>Necrosis damage</>.
A weaponized Originiutant mutant. Even more ferocious and terrifying than usual.
A heavy defender leader that has been controlled by an unknown entity, capable of regenerating rapidly.
Continually inflicts <@eb.key>Arts damage</> and <@eb.key>Nervous Impairment</> in an area around it; Has <@eb.key>status resistance</> and is immune to slowing effects.
Attacks in <@eb.key>Frigid</> areas deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</>; attacks in <@eb.key>Emergency Heater</> range deal <@eb.key>Physical damage</>.
Movement speed is reduced in <@eb.key>Emergency Heater</> range.
Immune to the effects of Mire; gains increased Movement Speed while in Mire
Ellen Select Technology Co. thanks you for your sponsorship! Knights, you're in for a <@eb.key>Surprise</> if you manage to shoot one down!
Prevents units from being deployed on current tile, effect nullified when destroyed
A basic melee soldier. They are equipped with armor that can withstand some Arts damage.
A basic guerrilla-ops war hound equipped with lightweight Sarkaz armor, having decent defenses while still being able to move quickly.
When on the same row or column with an allied unit, makes a <@eb.key>Straight Shot</>: fires 3 crossbow bolts.
Can only be blocked by units with at least 3 Block; first attack deals splash damage
The 'ultimate automaton' developed by the Liquor Association, with the power to 'squash ten kegs at the same time.'
Does not attack; Cannot be blocked; Must be damaged <@eb.key>35</> times to defeat.
Invisible; blinks forward a short distance when blocked
Starts with an additional 25 Energy, but loses 1 Energy per 5 seconds. When not blocked, uses ranged attacks that deal <@eb.key>AoE Physical damage</>. Energy Capacity: 30
Unknown age, gender, or background.
A Reunion squad leader who specializes in assassination and infiltration. She is able to <@eb.key>bypass</> Operators that try to block her.
A delinquent from Dossoles. Agile and nimble. Has a chance to dodge ranged Physical attacks when not blocked
A Reunion squad leader who <@eb.key>cannot be blocked</>. He launches long-ranged physical attacks and can spawn <@eb.key>turrets</> around the battlefield.
His duty is the one thing he still remembers. Spends ammo to deal <@eb.key>heavy Physical damage</>; becomes stunned for several seconds when his <@eb.key>reload</> is interrupted.
Leaves Carmine Steam at its location when defeated
Stronger in combat than the average Hound. When <@eb.key>Refraction</> is active, RES +70
Throws a Hot Spring 'Jolly Rascal' on first attack
Attacks in <@eb.key>Frigid</> areas deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</>; attacks in <@eb.key>Emergency Heater</> range deal <@eb.key>Physical damage</>.
Periodically deals True Damage to units in contact. Charges energy for Ishar'mla if no damage is dealt.
A Reunion melee soldier who has higher defensive abilities.
The leader of the Yeti Squadron. For the sake of this final battle, she has unleashed the remainder of what little life she has left.

name.m_value: Out of Control Sky Pole - Jia

description.m_value: Starts as a Friendly Unit monitoring the Blight level of the paddy. When the current paddy's <@eb.key>Blight level exceeds the threshold</>, wakes up and gradually loses HP. For every certain percentage of HP lost, releases a certain number of <@eb.key>Out of Control Sky Poles - Yi</>
An inmate well-versed in the Mansfield State Prison's rules of survival. After being freed, gains <@eb.key>increased ATK</>.
A robot surfing instructor that can take the wind and waves. Can <@eb.key>stop <Self-Driving Carts></>; takes significantly reduced Physical and Arts damage when not blocked.
Normally does not attack, but counters when attacked.
Attacks deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</>, and restore HP proportional to damage dealt.
One of Reunion's basic melee soldiers.
Pancho Salas, an old veteran piloting a heavily modified motorboat. Even should his vessel be destroyed, he will never falter before reaching his goal.
A caster who controls stone. Emerging from the darkness of Victoria, she has sworn to repay the humiliation she suffered at the hands of the nobles manyfold.
Each time an enemy is defeated, gains <@eb.key>ATK</> and <@eb.key>ASPD</>, stacking up to 10 times.
While under the <@eb.key>'Asset Liquidation'</> status, attacks are converted into Arts damage.
A well-trained Reunion rushing unit, more dangerous than a normal Break, that has high movement speed and <@eb.key>above average ATK</>.
Part of the Nachzehrer army. Releases <@eb.key>Corruption</> when defeated, causing your nearby units to continuously lose HP.
Much more robust than regular dockworkers. Can <@eb.key>Stun</> player's units after a few attacks. Quickly loses HP while under the effects of 'Erosion'
Phalanx Infantry near each other will support one another, <@eb.key>increasing their DEF</>. When <@eb.key>Refraction</> is active, RES +70
Covers its crown in protective boulders. <@eb.key>Weak spot</> located on its <@eb.key>rear</>, damage dealt to the front significantly decreased.
Soldier whose fate is entwined with the delegation, employing hardened and ruthless tactics. They are on guard against potential escalation.
Guide and pioneer of we many. Absorbing <@eb.key>Offspring</> increases its HP and ATK. After losing a certain percentage of HP, inflicts Stun and deals Arts damage to allies.
An independent Kazimierz knight who relies on more sophisticated equipment for defenses and utilizes a slow-and-steady strategy.
A product of Dorothy's failed experiments. Even though it fell far below expectations, she remains ever hopeful.
An infected wild creature that is more dangerous than an Originium Slug α.
After charging for some time, deals Arts damage to all units surrounding the target. While charging, loses <@eb.key>invisibility</>.
When unblocked, damage taken is reduced by 50%
A reckless Ink Spirit. Rushes forward single-mindedly, its surroundings be damned. <@eb.key>Can only be blocked by units of the same attribute</>.
A special Yeti Squadron elite melee combatant, capable of inflicting catastrophic damage to <@eb.key>Frozen</> units
A patch of shadow. It has never once left, nor has it ever truly existed.
An Infected creature commonly found in the lakes and rivers of Kazimierz.
Leaves Carmine Steam at its location when defeated
Deals massive physical damage to the Operator with the <@eb.key>highest Max HP</>; greatly decreases the ATK of, and deals continuous Arts damage to the Operator with the <@eb.key>lowest Max HP</>
鼠王BOSS，使用流沙的法师
A mercenary from Sarkaz who boasts <@eb.key>fairly high ATK and RES</> and uses <@eb.key>ranged Arts attacks</>. They are known to use Arts Chains to <@eb.key>disable Operators.</>
She sings no more. It speaks for we many. Leaves <@eb.key>Ishar'mla's Tears</> to charge for transformation. Deploy characters on <@eb.key>Ishar'mla's Tears</> to stop charging.
A powerful warrior who has flocked to the Guide, inspired by his philosophy. Fights to bring the common goal of the Pathfinders to fruition.
Deals heavy Physical damage to units on tiles affected by [Dominion]; continually generates [Dominion] in a certain radius around self
The Host of the Crimson Court, and master of all bloodborn.
Does not attack; after being attacked, runs away a random distance and rests for a period of time.
Spawns '<@eb.key>Nethersea Brand</>' and leaves behind <@eb.key>Remains</> at its location when defeated; [Directed Evolution] Increased RES.
Attacks two targets at once. Can stop attacking to incite hatred and continually increase <@eb.key>'Blood Debt'</>.
If <@eb.key>Movement Speed</> is higher than starting speed, gains <@eb.key>Low-Altitude Hovering</> and takes off!
Does not attack; Cannot be blocked; Must be damaged <@eb.key>3</> times to defeat.
Attacks deal <@eb.key>Arts damage</>; Upon death, deals <@eb.key>Arts damage</> to all surrounding units and inflicts <@eb.key>Cold</>; When shifted, loses HP proportional to the distance moved.
While in battle, reborn creations have <@eb.key>increased ATK</>, and their attacks will additionally deal <@eb.key>Necrosis damage</>.

The origin of a famous folk tale in Kazimierz. When taking damage, inflicts <@eb.key>Cold</> on the source of the damage. <@eb.key>Cold</> duration extended when HP is below 50%. ATK increased when attacking <@eb.key>Frozen</> targets.
A bona fide thug from the barrenlands, head to toe.
Takes up <@eb.key>3</> Block; Runs upon taking damage, significantly increasing <@eb.key>Movement Speed</> for a short time and dealing heavy damage to <@eb.key>Throttle Valves</> it passes over
A mercenary using ranged weaponry. <@eb.key>Uses ranged attacks</> and calls for the <@eb.key>advanced offensive Air Support Drone 'Scrap Model-U'</> to bombard the target.
Whenever a certain percentage of HP is lost, unleashes <@eb.key>permanent terrain effect 'Dominion'</>; Casts Arts 'Collapsing Fear', <@eb.key>instantly defeating</> units within 'Dominion'.
Your favorite cross-country beach buggy. Can only be blocked by units with Block 3 or higher. Can <@eb.key>carry up to 3 passengers</>.

An inmate who is proficient in Originium Arts, <@eb.key>increasing the ASPD of all enemies on the field</> when present. When imprisoned, <@eb.key>does not attack, but has increased DEF</>; After being freed, <@eb.key>attacks 2 targets at once</>; Prioritizes attacking Imprisonment Devices.
